16/02/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Federal Defence Minister Zoran Stankovic said on Wednesday (15 February) that he is prepared to resign if efforts under way to locate indictees wanted by the UN war crimes tribunal fail. 
According to the statement, the Military Intelligence Agency and other relevant bodies have stepped up activities to find the fugitives inside or outside Serbia. 
Stankovic stressed that if there were no concrete results within a reasonable period of time, he would assume responsibility for the failure and step down. 
(RTS, Beta, B92 - 15/02/06)
